<h2>Physics formula</h2>
<p>BlazorMotion uses a <strong>semi-implicit Euler</strong> integration:</p>
$$F = -k(x - x_0) - d \cdot v$$
$$v_{n+1} = v_n + (F/m) \cdot \Delta t \qquad x_{n+1} = x_n + v_{n+1} \cdot \Delta t$$
<p>For BounceSpring, the parameters are derived as:</p>
$$\omega_0 = \frac{2\pi}{T_{\text{visual}}} \qquad \zeta = \sqrt{1 - \text{bounce}^{2/3}}$$
$$k = \omega_0^2 \cdot m \qquad d = 2 \cdot \zeta \cdot \omega_0 \cdot m$$
